entries.title: miracleofsound
entries.description:
With over a billion completely grassroots cross platform streams, Miracle Of Sound is the project of Gavin Dunne, an independent producer/songwriter & singer from Ireland. The songs span a vast range of genres & styles, from dark folk to symphonic metal to sea shanties, cultivating a wide and varied audience over the last decade.

The project has had hundreds of chart appearances and a couple of ultra-viral hits, including the Viking history anthem Valhalla Calling, which has gone on to spawn countless cover versions, viral moments and remixes.

He has worked on cross promotion with various videogame industry companies including Ubisoft, Bioware, Owlcat/Games Workshop, EA and Bethesda for titles such as Mass Effect, Assassin’s Creed, Warhammer 40k, Wasteland 2 and Watch Dogs. 

Miracle Of Sound songs are loved for their addictive, catchy hooks, strong emotional punch and a ridiculously diverse range of genres, styles & song structures while always maintaining the MOS 'feel'.

entries.title: Games Done Quick
entries.description:
Games Done Quick showcases high-level gameplay, through its charity marathons, and its weekly content. 

Games Done Quick has a series of charity video game marathons. These events feature high-level gameplay by speedrunners raising money for charity. Teaming up with several charities in its ten-year history, Games Done Quick is currently the largest individual fundraising event globally for both Prevent Cancer Foundation and Doctors Without Borders USA.

To date, Games Done Quick has raised over 30 million dollars for charity. Our events average over 3000 people in attendance, including staff, volunteers, runners, and attendees!

The GDQ HOTFIX is our weekly speedrunning content, with over 20 different shows that showcase excellence in speedrunning and the community in different ways. If you're interested in speedruns, or speedrunning adjacent content, such as randomizers, high score challenges, and other challenge runs, check out https://gamesdonequick.com/hotfix

entries.title: Dr.Wily
entries.description:
Welcome to my channel Dr.Wily!

This channel mostly covers Nintendo games like Super Mario Bros and The Legend Of Zelda, and I upload 2 videos every week.

Our different types of videos:

Game Theories:
In these videos, we analyze the origin, timeline, secrets, mysteries, lore, history, powers and story of characters and events 
in Zelda and Super Mario.

Top 5 videos:
In these videos, we make a list of the 5 best, worst, most epic, etc things or characters in the Super Mario series or The Legend Of Zelda.

The Evolution Of:
In this series, we look at a specific enemy or character and see how they changed in terms of gameplay, use, design, and story throughout the years.

NOTE: Not all the theories on this channel where my idea, I get some of the video ideas from the site Zelda wiki, this only goes for the Zelda theories.
I also use Mariowikia and Zeldawikia a lot for the lore videos and general info.

To comply with COPPA, this channel is not intended for 13 years and younger.

entries.title: Next Game: Gaming Creation Show
entries.description:
Next Game is a video game podcast where two gamers create totally original sequels, prequels, and spin-offs of the best and worst video games of all time! They’ll cover anything from old, forgotten retro games to brand new, cutting edge franchises. Nintendo, PlayStation, Xbox or even Atari are all on the table! But the catch? Each host creates their own gaming concept in a head to head competition where only one will be crowned the winner by a special guest gamer acting as a producer!

Join Shane Luis & Adam Keresztyen from the YouTube channel Rerez (Just Bad Games, The Worst Ever Series) as they battle it out armed with their life long experiences and obsessions with the video game industry. Don’t miss a single episode as they try to make the Next Game!

Check out our main channel at: YouTube.com/@Rerez

entries.title: Nitro Rad
entries.description:
I'm James! A dude from Nova Scotia who's played platformers all his life. So I figured I'd start making videos about 3D platformers, both new and old! Though sometimes I'll cover weird indie games, horror games, or whatever else interests me.

I try to be thorough when discussing game mechanics. I like trying to figure out what makes something work. Though I also try to be fair and optimistic when it comes to reviewing older games. I think it's important to look for interesting aspects of art and design, even if the game isn't very good. Video games are interesting as hell, so I like seeing all the cool little things old janky games can hide.

entries.title: mikederp
entries.description:
Thanks for checking out MikeDerp!  Hello there, people! My name is Mike. 

On this channel, you'll find a new video posted at least once a week (Monday - could change) with my personal opinions on various videogames I've played and/or streamed over on Twitch. These are like mini review videos and will be without too many spoilers.

I'm here to help anyone who is looking to find a new game to play or If you're on the fence about a particular title, let me know and if I have played it I will do a Thoughts on Video which is my main series for the time being. Make sure to subscribe and leave a comment on a video saying “Yo, Derp!”.
